4 different games are played: monopoly, poker, snooker, scrabble
1. the police-officer and the person playing scrabble have the same parity positions##9
2. the person playing scrabble is not to the left of the police-officer##8
3. the fisherman is somewhere between the person playing monopoly and the person playing scrabble##7
4. the person playing scrabble is somewhere between the person playing snooker and the fisherman##7
5. the person playing poker is not the accountant##6
6. the police-officer is on the right of the fisherman##1
7. the analyst is in an even position##4

.:: Answer ::.
|               |   1    |   2   |   3   |    4    |
| Food          | accountant | fisherman | police-officer | analyst  |
| Music-Genre   | monopoly    | poker | scrabble | snooker |

